From: Dory maintainers <maintainers@dory.dev>
Subject: [PATCH] virtiofs: delegate permission checks to the file server

Dory's virtiofs server accesses bind-mounted files as the signed-in macOS
user. Container UIDs do not necessarily match that user's numeric UID, so
Linux mode checks can reject an operation that the backing macOS user is
allowed to perform before the request reaches the server.

Use the normal FUSE server-controlled permission model. Dory still reports
host UIDs and modes as metadata, while the backing filesystem remains the
authority for access.
---
 fs/fuse/virtio_fs.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/fs/fuse/virtio_fs.c b/fs/fuse/virtio_fs.c
index 8f5b3a4d3c8a..190e7c3aa822 100644
--- a/fs/fuse/virtio_fs.c
+++ b/fs/fuse/virtio_fs.c
@@ -1528 +1528 @@ static inline void virtio_fs_ctx_set_defaults(struct fuse_fs_context *ctx)
-	ctx->default_permissions = 1;
+	ctx->default_permissions = 0;
